The paper discusses the construction of quaternary sequences with low auto-correlation, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of interleaving method and cyclotomic classes also suggests a possible connection to data structures (cs.DS) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves the construction of sequences for code-division multiple access communication systems, which falls under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
